parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and engine stalling can cause accidents, especially when driving on busy highways, and can leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine shuts off
battery and oil lights pop on
loss of acceleration
vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Forward Collision Warning and Automatic Emergency Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the Forward Collision Warning and Automatic Emergency Braking System can cause sudden stops, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Forward Collision Warning engages and emergency brakes activate
vehicle comes to a sudden stop
warning lights and chimes activate without reason.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical issues and sonar malfunctions can cause unpredictable behavior, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Sonar alerts activate without reason
AEB and forward collision warning chime and alert without reason
vehicle stalls when backing up
electrical issues cause unpredictable behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can cause serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unexplained Vehicle Behavior and Software Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexplained vehicle behavior and software issues can cause accidents, injuries, and unpredictable behavior.
symptoms: Accelerator pedal fails to respond
door locks unlock independently
vehicle jolts and warning lights flash
heater
radio
and remote start fail to operate as designed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause hesitation, shuddering, and slipping when accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips
shudders
or hesitates when accelerating
the vehicle does not respond to accelerator input
the vehicle vibrates excessively
the collision light comes on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine performance issues can cause hesitation, lack of power, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine hesitates or stalls when accelerating
the vehicle lacks power when taking off
the engine makes a constant ticking noise
the engine may stop working at any time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The forward collision light warning issues can cause the driver to be unaware of potential hazards, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The forward collision light comes on intermittently
the vehicle's collision warning system is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the main air flow sensor can cause the vehicle to drive improperly, leading to a safety hazard for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The sensor malfunction light comes on
the check engine light is illuminated
and the vehicle may not drive properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting off can cause a safety risk, especially when driving at moderate to high speeds, as it can lead to accidents or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly slows down or stalls
the check engine light is illuminated
and the vehicle may shut off while driving or idling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling or Idling Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling or idling issues can cause a safety risk, especially when driving at moderate to high speeds, as it can lead to accidents or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The vehicle idles rough
the vehicle dies or stalls
and the vehicle may restart after several attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vent control valve can cause the engine to shut off while driving, leading to a safety hazard for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
and the vent control valve is stuck open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the forward collision system can cause the vehicle to brake unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents, especially at high speeds, and can also cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The forward collision warning light illuminates without any apparent reason
the vehicle brakes unexpectedly
the automatic braking system activates for no apparent reason
the vehicle slows down or stops suddenly
the driver experiences sudden and unexpected loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM or alternator can cause the vehicle to enter limp mode, which can lead to a loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on busy highways.
symptoms: The vehicle enters limp mode
the front crash sensors illuminate
the vehicle cuts out and then returns to limp mode
the vehicle's computer readout points to the front sensors
the alternator is reported to be failing.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Forward Collision Warning and Unintended Braking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the forward collision warning system can cause the vehicle to brake suddenly, increasing the risk of accidents or rear-end collisions, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The forward collision warning light flashes or illuminates without any obstacles or vehicles in front of the car
the vehicle suddenly brakes or slows down without any apparent reason
the alarm sounds
and the dashboard displays warning symbols or messages.
